<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Track 1 · Image Tagger Hub</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../ka_atlas_shell.css">
<style>:root { --hub-color: #8A5028; }</style>
</head>
<body data-ka-active="" data-ka-journey="contributor"
      data-ka-crumbs='[["Home","ka_home.html"],["Tracks","ka_track_picker.html"],["Image Tagger Hub",""]]' data-ka-regime="160sp">

<a class="ka-skip" href="#main">Skip to main content</a>
<div id="ka-navbar-slot"></div>
<div id="ka-breadcrumb-slot"></div>

<section class="hub-banner">
  <div class="tag">Track 1 · Team Hub</div>
  <h1>Image Tagger</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">
    Curate, crop, and annotate the image corpus that powers the Knowledge Atlas figure
    gallery. Each tagged image becomes a retrievable piece of visual evidence anchored
    to a specific claim in a specific article.
  </p>
  <p class="roster-count">Spring 2026 roster: 5 enrolled students</p>
</section>

<div class="ka-shell">
  <aside id="ka-journey-slot"></aside>

  <main id="ka-main">

    <div class="hub-regions">

      <section class="hub-region">
        <div class="hub-region-head"><div>
          <div class="hub-region-num">Region 1</div>
          <div class="hub-region-title">Environment setup</div>
        </div></div>
        <div class="hub-region-body">
          <ul>
            <li>Python 3.11+ with Pillow, pytesseract, and <code>imagehash</code></li>
            <li>Tesseract OCR installed (<code>brew install tesseract</code>)</li>
            <li>Zotero desktop, logged in to the course group</li>
            <li>Access to the shared figure cache directory (via UCSD VPN)</li>
          </ul>
<pre>git clone https://github.com/ucsd-cogs160/image_tagger.git
cd image_tagger
python3 -m venv .venv &amp;&amp; source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python3 scripts/verify_env.py</pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="hub-region">
        <div class="hub-region-head"><div>
          <div class="hub-region-num">Region 2</div>
          <div class="hub-region-title">Shared resources</div>
        </div></div>
        <div class="hub-region-body">
          <ul>
            <li>Figure-caption extraction templates</li>
            <li>Controlled-vocabulary tag list (spatial, material, thermal, social, cognitive…)</li>
            <li>Gold-standard tagged-image exemplars (10 cases with rationale)</li>
            <li>Duplicate-detection thresholds (perceptual hash distance)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="hub-region">
        <div class="hub-region-head"><div>
          <div class="hub-region-num">Region 3</div>
          <div class="hub-region-title">Ways of working</div>
        </div></div>
        <div class="hub-region-body">
          <ul>
            <li>One tagger owns one article at a time — 10–20 figures per article.</li>
            <li>Second tagger reviews before merge (kappa agreement target ≥ 0.7).</li>
            <li>Weekly Thursday sync to discuss edge cases and evolve the vocabulary.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="hub-region">
        <div class="hub-region-head"><div>
          <div class="hub-region-num">Region 4</div>
          <div class="hub-region-title">Task context &amp; manifests</div>
        </div></div>
        <div class="hub-region-body">

          <article class="task-manifest">
            <div class="task-manifest-head" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
              <span class="task-manifest-title">IT-001 · Extract and tag figures from a single article</span>
              <span class="task-manifest-status status-supported">Well-specified</span>
            </div>
            <div class="task-manifest-body">
              <dl>
                <dt>Goal</dt><dd>For one article, produce cleanly cropped PNGs of each
                  figure with metadata.</dd>
                <dt>Outputs</dt><dd><code>figures/&lt;article_id&gt;/figN.png</code> and
                  <code>figures/&lt;article_id&gt;/manifest.json</code> with caption, tags,
                  and claim-anchor.</dd>
                <dt>Acceptance</dt><dd>All figures in the source PDF extracted; each
                  tagged with ≥ 2 controlled-vocabulary terms; each linked to a
                  specific claim sentence in the article record.</dd>
                <dt>Verification</dt><dd>Automated: <code>verify_tags.py &lt;article_id&gt;</code>
                  checks schema, count parity with PDF, perceptual-hash uniqueness.</dd>
              </dl>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="task-manifest">
            <div class="task-manifest-head" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
              <span class="task-manifest-title">IT-002 · Vocabulary consolidation pass</span>
              <span class="task-manifest-status status-partial">Partially specified</span>
            </div>
            <div class="task-manifest-body">
              <dl>
                <dt>Goal</dt><dd>Review tags across the existing corpus, collapse
                  near-synonyms, propose new terms.</dd>
                <dt>Verification</dt><dd>Manual plus a test that every live tag appears
                  in the authoritative vocabulary file.</dd>
              </dl>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="hub-region">
        <div class="hub-region-head"><div>
          <div class="hub-region-num">Region 5</div>
          <div class="hub-region-title">Functional verification</div>
        </div></div>
        <div class="hub-region-body">
          <p>Grading is by <strong>harness pass</strong>, not aesthetic judgment.
          A tag submission is accepted when:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Manifest JSON validates against <code>contracts/figure_manifest.schema.json</code></li>
            <li>Every image file exists and is &ge; 400 px on the long edge</li>
            <li>Every tag is in the authoritative vocabulary</li>
            <li>No two images in the same article have perceptual-hash distance &lt; 6</li>
          </ul>
<pre>python3 scripts/verify_tags.py bratman_2019
# → 14 figures, schema OK, 14/14 images present, 28 tags all in vocab → PASS</pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="hub-region">
        <div class="hub-region-head"><div>
          <div class="hub-region-num">Region 6</div>
          <div class="hub-region-title">Help &amp; queue</div>
        </div></div>
        <div class="hub-region-body">
          <div class="help-queue">
            <h5>Where to ask for help</h5>
            <ul>
              <li><code>#track1-image-tagger</code> Slack</li>
              <li>Office hours: Thursdays 2–3 pm, CSB 155</li>
              <li>Ambiguous tag → add to the Thursday-sync discussion queue</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</div>

<footer class="ka-footer">
  Knowledge Atlas · UCSD Cognitive Science · COGS 160 Spring 2026
</footer>

<script src="../ka_canonical_navbar.js" defer></script>
<script src="../ka_journey_nav.js"      defer></script>
</body>
</html>
